            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Was here for Civils prelims examination, very disappointed with the approach of the Institute admin and the District authorities about the arrangements made for the examination. Despite being an international school in tag, they failed to provide Cloak Room for keeping the belongings of the candidates who came from long distances, we were forced to keep backpacks and valuable belongings in it, outside the building, open to the sky, which got dirty by some dirty water flooded in the place during the afternoon paper. There were no arrangements for the candidate to sit or wait anywhere, all were forced to sit on the side of the outside road. Esp when the exam is from Morning to evening, these arrangements are well required, which were not fulfilled. Complete failure from the side of School and district admns. And another joke is, the school's washroom has no water pipe or wash basin inside the common toilets! While there was a fountain beside the entrance of the building.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
